==病理生理學==
{{seealso|腎功能|腎生理學}}
<!--
The exact pathologic mechanism for RCN is unclear, however the onset of small vessel pathology is likely an important aspect in the etiology of this condition.  In general the renal cortex is under greater oxygen tension and more prone to ischemic injury, especially at the level of the proximal [[Collecting_duct_system|collecting tubule]], leading to its preferential damage in a sudden drop in perfusion.  Rapidly corrected acute renal ischemia leads to [[acute_tubular_necrosis|acute tubular necrosis]], from which complete recovery is possible, while more prolonged ischemia may lead to RCN.  Pathologically, the cortex of the kidney is grossly atrophied with relative preservation of the gross structure of the medulla.  The damage is usually bilateral owing to its underlying systemic causes, and is most frequently associated with pregnancy (>50% of cases).<ref name="Medscape">{{Cite web |last1 =Deverajan  |first1 =Prasad  |editor= Langman, Craig B |title = eMedicine: Renal Cortical Necrosis | url =http://emedicine.medscape.com/article/983599 | publisher = Medscape | date = May 26, 2011  | accessdate = 27 March 2012}}</ref> It accounts for 2% of all cases of acute renal failure in adults and more than 20% of cases of acute renal failure during late pregnancy.<ref>{{cite journal|title=Acute kidney injury in late pregnancy in developing countries|pages=309–313|issn=1525-6049|journal=Renal Failure|volume=32|issue=3|date=2010-1|doi=10.3109/08860221003606265|url=https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/20370445|accessdate=2019-02-12|author=Jai Prakash, Shashidhar Shree Niwas, Aashish Parekh, Laxmi Kant Pandey, Loukrakpam Sharatchandra, Puneet Arora, Amit Kumar Mahapatra|pmid=20370445}}</ref><ref>{{cite journal|title=Acute renal failure in pregnancy|pages=333–351|issn=0950-3552|journal=Bailliere's Clinical Obstetrics and Gynaecology|volume=8|issue=2|date=1994-6|url=https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/7924011|accessdate=2019-02-12|author=N. Pertuiset, J. P. Grünfeld|pmid=7924011}}<